  "response": "No, the Stark Malibu mansion, as depicted in the Iron Man movies in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, is not a real mansion. It is a fictional location created for the films. The exterior of the mansion was created using CGI. Some interior shots were filmed at real locations, such as the Point Dume estate in Malibu, while others were shot on sets built by the production team. Consequently, while it appears to be a stunning real mansion on screen, the Stark Malibu mansion does not exist in reality.",
